<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEMORIES OF WOMEN WHO INSPIRED HER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jane Garrison's article about Nellie Bly ("Nellie Bly, Girl Reporter," March 
28) took me back to my childhood in the '50s and '60s when I was a voracious 
reader of biographies.Women such as Nellie Bly, Amelia Earhart, Madame Curie, 
Clara Barton and (Unsinkable) Molly Brown became my heroes. They excited my 
imagination with their intelligence, daring and perseverance. 
</P>
<P>
 Although I am not daring, I followed in their footsteps in my own quiet way by 
becoming a licensed traffic engineer with a bachelor of science degree in civil 
engineering. 
</P>
<P>
 RUTH M. SMITH 
</P>
<P>
 Monterey Park 
</P>
