<P>
COMING TO A THEATER NEAR YOU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID J. FOX 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some of the summer's anticipated independently released films: 
</P>
<P>
 June 3: "Endless Summer II: The Journey Continues" (New Line). The sequel to 
the '60s surfing saga. 
</P>
<P>
 June 10: "Go Fish" (Goldwyn). A comedy about lesbian life by women who live 
it. 
</P>
<P>
 June 17: "White" (Miramax). Part of Krzysztos Kieslowski's trilogy of love 
stories, "Trois Couleurs." 
</P>
<P>
 July 15: "Mi Vida Loca" (Sony Classics). Alison Anders directs a story about 
Latina homegirls. 
</P>
<P>
 July 22: "Exit to Eden" (Savoy). Starring Dana Delany, Paul Mecurio, Dan 
Aykroyd, Rosie O'Donnell in the film version of Anne Rice's novel. 
</P>
<P>
 July 29: "The Mask" (New Line). Jim Carrey stars in an action-comedy with 
special effects. 
</P>
<P>
 "Camilla" (Miramax). Jessica Tandy and Bridget Fonda star. 
</P>
<P>
 Aug. 5: "Eat, Drink, Man, Woman" (Goldwyn). A romantic comedy from director 
Ang Lee of "The Wedding Banquet." 
</P>
<P>
 Aug. 19: "Corrina, Corrina" (New Line). Whoopi Goldberg and Ray Liotta star in 
a comedy about finding love and family in unlikely places.  
</P>
<P>
 Undated: "S.F.W." (Gramercy). Stephen Dorff, Reese Witherspoon team up in this 
satiric commentary about fame.  
</P>
<P>
 Undated: "The Beans of Egypt, Maine" (IRS Media). Kelly Lynch, Martha Plimpton 
star. 
</P>
<P>
 Undated: "Little Buddha" (Miramax). Director Bernardo Bertolucci's latest, 
starring Keanu Reeves.  
</P>
<P>
 Undated: "Pulp Fiction" (Miramax). Bruce Willis, John Travolta and Uma Thurman 
star in director Quentin Tarantino's drama. DAVID J. FOX 
</P>
