<HEADLINE>
<P>
VIKTOR G. AFANASYEV; WAS EDITOR OF PRAVDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Viktor G. Afanasyev, 70, editor of the Soviet newspaper Pravda from 1976 to 
1989.A prominent journalist under Soviet Union leaders from Leonid Brezhnev to 
Mikhail Gorbachev, Afanasyev was considered chief spokesman, through the 
influential newspaper, of the Communist Party. Also a deputy in the Soviet 
parliament, Afanasyev was known as an intellectual, a scholar and a 
philosopher. He served in the Soviet Army during World War II and was an 
administrator in education before joining Pravda in 1968. The newspaper's 
circulation was 13 million during his tenure as editor. On Sunday in Moscow. 
</P>
