<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; CITY 'CULTURAL MASTER PLAN TO BE 
DISCUSSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Proposals for a citywide "cultural master plan" will be discussed Thursday at 
6:30 p.m. at a meeting in the City Council Chamber, 2000 Main St. The public is 
invited. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wolf Organization, a cultural planning firm, has been studying cultural 
and historic resources in Huntington Beach for the past six months. 
Representatives of the organization will present their preliminary findings 
during the Thursday night meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents will be given the opportunity to express their views on the various 
proposals. 
</P>
<P>
 Additional information about the meeting may be obtained by calling the city's 
Cultural Services Division, (714) 536-5258. BILL BILLITER 
</P>
