<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJOR LEAGUES; CUBS TRADE BOSKIE FOR MINOR 
LEAGUER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Chicago Cubs traded right-hander Shawn Boskie to the Philadelphia Phillies 
for minor league pitcher Kevin Foster and will recall reliever Chuck Crim from 
triple-A Iowa to fill the roster spot. 
</P>
<P>
 Boskie had spent three-plus seasons with the Cubs and in two appearances this 
season was 0-0 with a 0.00 ERA.He was 5-3 with a 3.43 ERA last season when he 
made two starts. He is 19-29 in 107 appearances, including 55 starts. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Holly Minter, 26, was in serious condition in a Dallas hospital, recovering 
from broken ribs and a broken right arm sustained in a fall from the upper deck 
on opening day Monday at The Ballpark in Arlington. . . . . First baseman Kevin 
Maas, who hit 21 home runs in three months in a record-setting rookie season 
with the New York Yankees, signed a minor league contract with the San Diego 
Padres. Maas, who will play at double-A Wichita, was released by the Yankees 
during spring training. 
</P>
