<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; WAREHOUSE OWNER GETS $5,600 TAX BREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A wholesale compact disc and music video distributor that recently bought a 
$1.3-million Simi Valley warehouse has been granted a $5,600 tax break by the 
city. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council agreed to grant Pacific Coast One-Stop the assistance, 
usually reserved for new construction projects, because the company is making 
$500,000 in improvements to the property. 
</P>
<P>
 City Manager Lin Koester urged the council to approve the tax reduction, 
pointing out that the warehouse Pacific Coast bought at 45 W. Easy St. has been 
a constant headache for the city. 
</P>
<P>
 The site is the former home of Travelin' West Textiles, a dyeing facility that 
had a long history of waste-water violations, illegally disgorging up to 
500,000 gallons of polluted water each day for more than a decade before 
closing in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
 "That site has been a problem site and we're actually very thankful that 
Pacific Coast is going ahead with this," Koester said. 
</P>
<P>
 The council agreed, unanimously approving the tax break. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
