<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOROWSKI LEAVES ANAHEIM FOR WALNUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Anaheim football Coach Todd Borowski has resigned to coach at Walnut High, 
Borowski said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Borowski led the Colonists to the Southern Section Division VI quarterfinals 
in the last two seasons. Anaheim was 15-9 under Borowski. 
</P>
<P>
 In his first season in 1992, Borowski led the Colonists to a 9-3 record and a 
share of the Orange League championship. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the Colonists reached the playoffs again in 1993, new facilities at 
Walnut and an opportunity to coach with former Cal State Fullerton classmate 
Ron Sparicino helped persuade him to move. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA041394-0101 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 031762 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
