<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 7; Column 5; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
217 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; TRABUCO HILLS BOUNCES CENTURY IN 11TH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brian Costello, Trabuco Hills' No. 8 batter, singled in a run in the bottom of 
the 11th inning to give the Mustangs a 3-2 victory over Century in a Pacific 
Coast League baseball game Tuesday in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 With one out in the 11th, Dan Delfium singled and stole second.Costello worked 
the count to three and one before singling down the right-field line for the 
winning run. 
</P>
<P>
 Costello played a part in each of the Mustangs runs. In the third inning, he 
tripled home Delfium and scored on a sacrifice fly by Gerry Beckham to give 
Trabuco Hills (11-5, 6-0 in league) a 2-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Century (11-4, 4-2), which had gotten the lead-off hitter on base in five of 
the first six innings, tied the score in the sixth. The Centurions loaded the 
bases on an infield single by Art Tapia, a double by Jerry Ochoa and a walk to 
Christian Duran. Mustang reliever Ryan Kelley entered and got Ramiro Torres to 
hit into a double play, scoring Tapia. A single by Richard Cevallos tied the 
score before Kelley got the last out. Kelley (6-1) allowed three hits in six 
innings of relief. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills had a chance to win the game in the seventh when it loaded the 
bases, but a fly out by Matt Rechner ended the inning. 
</P>
<P>
 The two teams meet for a third time this season on Friday at Century. MIKE 
WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
