<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; MILLER, SCOTT LEAD MASTER'S OVER POMONA IN SLUGFEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Justin Miller had four hits, including two homers, to lead The Master's 
College to a 17-10 victory over Pomona-Pitzer in a nonconference baseball game 
Tuesday at The Master's. 
</P>
<P>
 David Scott also had four hits for The Master's (10-24-2) and drove in three 
runs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mustangs trailed, 6-3, after three innings but scored eight runs in the 
fourth to take an 11-6 lead. Master's also scored two runs in each of the 
sixth, seventh and eighth innings. 
</P>
<P>
 The teams combined for 37 hits, with Master's knocking out 24. 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard 11, Glendale 1 -- Chad Olthoff (4-1) pitched a five-hitter for Oxnard, 
walking one and striking out one. 
</P>
<P>
 The fifth-inning run was unearned. 
</P>
<P>
 Jess Oliveras was three for four and drove in two runs for the Condors (13-15, 
7-7 in Western State Conference play). 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Anderson's two-run double in the first began Oxnard's scoring and the 
Condors added eight runs in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 Pierce 6, Santa Barbara 3 -- First baseman Kevin Milligan had three hits and 
drove in three runs to lead the Brahmas in a WSC game. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore left-hander Adam West (6-4) pitched a complete game for Pierce 
(17-12, 9-5), allowing 10 hits while striking out four. 
</P>
<P>
 The Brahmas scored three runs in the top of the ninth to take a 6-2 lead 
before Santa Barbara scored a run in the bottom half. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 10, Santa Monica 3 -- George Macias doubled and singled with three 
runs batted in, leading the Pirates (17-12, 7-7) to a WSC victory at Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Jamal Nichols, Clint Harris and David Frazier each had two hits for Ventura. 
Frazier and Harris each scored two runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Brandon Knight (2-2), a Buena High graduate, pitched six innings of relief, 
giving up only one run to pick up the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica's Javier Durazo had two doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Bakersfield 5, Moorpark 4 -- The Renegades scored three runs in the fifth 
inning and held on for a WSC victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore Aaron Fischer had a double, the only extra-base hit among six hits 
for Moorpark (13-13-2, 6-6).  
</P>
<P>
 Bakersfield pounded out 13 hits. 
</P>
<P>
 San Bernardino Valley 16, Antelope Valley 3 -- Steve Ogden hit his Foothill 
Conference-leading 10th home run of the season, leading the Indians (18-12, 
11-3) at San Bernardino. 
</P>
<P>
 San Bernardino Valley outhit Antelope Valley, 17-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Wilson was the losing pitcher for the Marauders (11-11, 5-8). 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Bowne led Antelope Valley's offense with two RBIs. SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran 8-5, La Verne 3-2 -- The Regals allowed 22 hits in the 
doubleheader but improved to 17-7, 13-0 in the Southern California 
Intercollegiate Athletic Conference with a sweep.  
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran scored five runs in the fourth inning in the opener.  
</P>
<P>
 In the second game, winning pitcher Xochitl Castillo (6-1) hit a two-run 
double during a four-run first inning. 
</P>
