<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP VOLLEYBALL ROUNDUP; LOW-KEY NEWPORT HARBOR WINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Less was more for Newport Harbor Coach Dan Glenn as the Sailors, ranked sixth 
in Orange County, defeated ninth-ranked Corona del Mar, 15-13, 12-15, 15-9, 
15-10, in a Sea View League boys' volleyball match Tuesday at Corona del Mar 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think I did too much coaching in the first two games," Glenn said, "instead 
of keeping my mouth shut and letting the kids play." 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Vallely, who split time between setter and outside hitter, had 12 kills 
and 39 assists to lead Newport Harbor (8-2, 7-0 in league), which broke open a 
match that was close early. 
</P>
<P>
 Reserves Ramy Shoukry and Paul Root also gave the Sailors a lift. 
</P>
<P>
 Shoukry and Root had four blocks each to help slow Corona del Mar's attack. 
Shoukry also finished with nine kills and Root had six. 
</P>
<P>
 "That must have been the match of the season for Ramy," Corona del Mar Coach 
Joey Fuschetti said. "We played well but Newport Harbor played better." 
</P>
<P>
 Brooks Hoppe had 21 kills and four blocks, Brian Coleman had 15 kills, and 
Brad Callahan had 10 for the Sea Kings (7-2, 5-2). But Newport Harbor won with 
better balance. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to Vallely, Shoukry and Root, Wes Badorek (13 kills), Mitch McCoy 
(11), and Greg Slick (10) also contributed. 
</P>
<P>
 After the teams split the first two games, Slick had four kills to help the 
Sailors grab a 9-1 lead in Game 3. Corona del Mar never got closer than 14-9, 
and McCoy blocked Hoppe on game point. 
</P>
<P>
 In Game 4, Corona del Mar trailed, 10-9, but Newport Harbor scored five of the 
last six points to win the match. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
