<HEADLINE>
<P>
3.2 AFTERSHOCK GIVES NEWHALL ANOTHER JOLT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 3.2-magnitude aftershock from the Northridge earthquake rattled Newhall on 
Tuesday evening, further fraying the nerves of temblor-weary residents but 
otherwise causing no injuries or damage. 
</P>
<P>
 The aftershock, at 6:57 p.m., was centered four miles southwest of Newhall, 
according to Caltech seismologist Robby Robb. 
</P>
