<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHALLENGERS ROUT 2 TUSTIN COUNCIL INCUMBENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an upset election, two challengers soundly defeated Council members Leslie 
Anne Pontious and Charles E. Puckett in Tuesday's municipal elections. 
</P>
<P>
 Tracy Worley and Michael J. Doyle each received well over 600 votes more than 
the incumbents, according to unofficial results. 
</P>
<P>
 "Obviously I'm very happy," Worley said. 
</P>
<P>
 An electronic counting machine broke down during the count, delaying results 
and forcing the city to bring in a machine from Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 In the campaign, the incumbents said that planning for the future reuse of the 
Tustin Marine Corps Air Station is the most critical decision City Council 
members will face in the next four years. 
</P>
<P>
 Pontious and Puckett contended that the city was in good hands under the 
current council, whose other members are Mayor Jim Potts and Councilmen Thomas 
R. Saltarelli and Jeffrey Thomas. Crime is down, sales tax income is up, new 
businesses are coming in, and while nearby cities struggle to maintain 
services, Tustin is financially healthy, they said. 
</P>
<P>
 But Doyle and Worley said that the more important issues were the city 
attorney's fees, a gift ban for council members, term limits and limits on 
campaign contribution. 
</P>
<P>
 "We need to have more accountability," Doyle said. He said that Pontious and 
Puckett failed to order a thorough review of city credit expenses last year 
even after allegations surfaced that high-ranking officials of the Police 
Department were using city credit cards to charge meals and gifts. 
</P>
<P>
 The challengers had criticized Puckett for using city credit cards for 
business lunches with City Manager William A. Huston in 1991 and 1992 at a 
Fullerton restaurant that featured female models in scanty clothing. Puckett 
said the meetings were strictly business. 
</P>
<P>
 An audit later indicated that there was no widespread abuse. EDITION TIME 
ELECTION RETURNS 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin City Council 
</P>
<P>
 2 Elected 
</P>
<P>
 100% Precincts Reporting: Votes (%) Tracy Worley: 2,516 (30.4) Michael J. 
Doyle: 2,386 (28.8) Leslie Anne Pontious*: 1,700 (20.5) Charles E. Puckett*: 
1,672 (20.2) 
</P>
<P>
 * Incumbent 
</P>
<P>
 Elected candidates are in bold type. 
</P>
