<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; INMATE STABBED IN BRAWL AT COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A prisoner was stabbed in the chest with a knife made from a razor blade after 
a fight broke out in a lockup while he was waiting to appear in court, 
authorities said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 More than a dozen black and Latino inmates fought in a racially motivated 
brawl at Newhall Municipal Court about noon Monday. No deputies were hurt 
during the two-minute incident, said a sheriff's deputy. 
</P>
<P>
 The injured inmate, James Jaspar, 29, was taken to Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial 
Hospital in Valencia. He was treated for stab wounds to the chest and returned 
to the County Jail. 
</P>
<P>
 Two other inmates, Patrick Contreras, 19, and Edward Espinoza, 22, were booked 
on suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon. 
</P>
