</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Susan Christian Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cutting Quake Damage: A large earthquake could put a lot of small companies 
out of business.The Brea Fire Department will offer tips Thursday on how to 
alleviate damage in the event of a quake. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire Department officials will talk about how to reduce injuries, protect your 
equipment and expedite the resumption of business should an earthquake hit 
Orange County. The program will be from 7:30 to 9:30 a.m. at the Brea Civic & 
Cultural Center. The cost is $20. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 990-7622. 
</P>
