</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are searching for a 57-year-old, brain-injured man who walked away from 
a Laguna Hills board and care facility Sunday night. The man, John K. Sorensen, 
was injured in a 1991 auto accident. 
</P>
<P>
 Sorensen is 6-foot-1, weighs about 180 pounds and walks with a limp, according 
to Lt. Dan Martini of the Orange County Sheriff's Department. He has blue eyes 
and gray hair, worn in a crew cut. 
</P>
