<TEXT>
<P>
 CPR -- The "6 Steps to Saving a Life" story in Tuesday's View should have 
included the following instructions for performing CPR: After every 15 chest 
compressions, the rescuer should give two slow mouth-to-mouth breaths to the 
victim. The chest pumps and breaths should be alternated at this pace until 
emergency medical help arrives. 
